cal programs than is typically assumed. He concludes that when a single interest group dominates the political process, judicial intervention to determine a program's legal validity may be appropriate. But if the political contest involves competing groups, courts should defer to local political judgments.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aDistribution (Economic theory). 0aLocal financezUnited States. 0aLocal governmentzUnited States. 7aLAW / Government / State, Provincial & Municipal.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030012565840uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030017182240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300171822423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300171822/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY